

Node Packages :
---------------------------- >
>> A package is a reusable piece of code (library/module) that solves a specific problem.

> we can work with the individual file with the node, But , individual file depends on other file and 
..... etc , then dependencies become more challenges.

Why we need to packages:
-------------------------------- >
> Avoid writing everything from scratch
> Reuse community-tested code.
> Faster developement
Problem without Packages:
--------------------------------- >
> Managing dependencies manually becomes complex
> Version conflicts
> Hard to scale projects



Package.json:
---------------- >
> It is an bluePrint of the current packages and all its dependencies.
> In the packages we have the versioning
   lets say :
 EX:   Semantic Versioning
   "fetch" :  "^1.1.0",   1. major ,   1. minor,  .0 patch
   >> Means install version 1.1.0 or later but do not go beyond major release 1. ,
  anything after 1.1.0 and under <2.0.0
  
"fetch" : "~7.6.0"
  >> Means install version 7.6.0 or later but donot go beyond minor 6 
  >> That is anything after 7.6.0 and under <7.7.0 


